<h5 class="tight"><font face="Lucida Grande,Helvetica,Arial">Discussion</font>
</h5><p><!-- begin discussion --><br><br>
As can be seen in PropagateInObject(), photons are always moved in two steps to avoid round off 
errors due to moving photons to an interface and crossing it when we are not supposed to (or not crossing
when we expect the photon to).  This should be "irrelevantly" small.  Currently, it is 10 nm.<!-- end discussion --></p>
